---
layout: base.njk
title: Map
description: Explore Scripture locations with Paul's journeys, early churches, and chapter-level places.
permalink: /map/
---

<div class="map-page">
  <section class="map-workspace" id="map-workspace">
    <div class="map-workspace-header">
      <div class="map-workspace-title">
        <span class="map-badge">Map Beta</span>
        <h1 class="map-title">Map</h1>
        <p>
          Map turns where into a study tool. Follow Paul's journeys, surface key early churches, and
          connect passages to geography without losing the reading-first experience.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="map-workspace-stats" aria-label="Map scope">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">4</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Journey routes</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts 13-28</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">50+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Places</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">MVP scope</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">8</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Church hubs</div>
          <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts + epistles</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-shell">
      <aside class="map-panel" aria-label="Journey controls">
        <div class="map-panel-header">
          <div>
            <div class="map-kicker">Journey overview</div>
            <h3 id="journeyTitle">Loading journey...</h3>
            <p id="journeyMeta">Acts • 0 stops</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-panel-controls" role="group" aria-label="Select journey">
            <button class="map-pill" type="button" data-journey="jn_pauls_first">Journey 1</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button" data-journey="jn_pauls_second">Journey 2</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button" data-journey="jn_pauls_third">Journey 3</button>
            <button class="map-pill" type="button" data-journey="jn_to_rome">To Rome</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <section class="map-place-card" id="mapPlaceCard" aria-live="polite">
          <div class="map-place-empty">Select a stop to see details.</div>
        </section>

        <div class="map-controls" role="group" aria-label="Journey playback">
          <button class="map-action" type="button" data-action="prev">Previous</button>
          <button class="map-action primary" type="button" data-action="play" aria-pressed="false">
            Play
          </button>
          <button class="map-action" type="button" data-action="next">Next</button>
        </div>

        <ol
          class="map-stop-list"
          id="mapStopList"
          role="listbox"
          aria-label="Journey stops"
        ></ol>

        <div class="map-panel-footer">
          <div class="map-churches-card">
            <div class="map-churches-header">
              <div>
                <h4>Ancient churches</h4>
                <p>Antioch, Corinth, Ephesus, Philippi, Thessalonica, Rome.</p>
              </div>
              <button class="map-action small" type="button" data-action="toggle-church-list">
                Browse churches
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="map-churches-list" id="mapChurchList" hidden></div>
          <div class="map-church-profile" id="mapChurchProfile" hidden></div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="map-canvas">
        <div class="map-toolbar">
          <div class="map-toolbar-left">
            <button
              class="map-toolbar-btn map-anchor-btn"
              type="button"
              data-action="anchor-view"
              aria-label="Return to anchor view"
            >
              Return to anchor
            </button>
            <div class="map-search-wrap">
              <input
                class="map-search"
                id="mapSearchInput"
                type="search"
                placeholder="Search: Ephesus, Efes, Selcuk"
                aria-label="Search places or regions"
                autocomplete="off"
              />
              <div class="map-search-results" id="mapSearchResults" role="listbox"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="map-toolbar-actions">
            <div class="map-layers-control">
              <button
                class="map-toolbar-btn"
                type="button"
                data-action="layers"
                aria-haspopup="true"
                aria-expanded="false"
              >
                Layers
              </button>
              <div class="map-layers-popover" id="mapLayersPopover" role="dialog" hidden>
                <div class="map-layers-header">
                  <span>Layers</span>
                  <button
                    class="map-layers-close"
                    type="button"
                    data-action="close-layers"
                    aria-label="Close layers"
                  >
                    ×
                  </button>
                </div>
                <label class="map-layer-toggle">
                  <input type="checkbox" data-layer="journeys" checked />
                  <span>Journeys</span>
                </label>
                <label class="map-layer-toggle">
                  <input type="checkbox" data-layer="churches" />
                  <span>Churches</span>
                </label>
                <label class="map-layer-toggle">
                  <input type="checkbox" data-layer="modern_labels" />
                  <span>Modern labels</span>
                </label>
                <label class="map-layer-toggle">
                  <input type="checkbox" data-layer="base_labels" checked />
                  <span>Base labels</span>
                </label>
                <div class="map-layer-group">
                  <div class="map-layer-title">Coming soon</div>
                  <label class="map-layer-toggle disabled">
                    <input type="checkbox" disabled />
                    <span>Boundaries</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="map-layer-toggle disabled">
                    <input type="checkbox" disabled />
                    <span>People groups</span>
                  </label>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <button class="map-toolbar-btn" type="button" data-action="bookmark-view">
              Bookmark view
            </button>
            <span class="map-toolbar-pill map-era" aria-disabled="true">Era: Acts</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="map-canvas-stage">
          <div id="map" class="maplibre-map" role="application" aria-label="Interactive map"></div>
          <div class="map-confidence" id="mapConfidence">Confidence: High</div>
          <div class="map-point-popover" id="mapPointPopover" hidden>
            <button
              class="map-point-close"
              type="button"
              data-action="close-point"
              aria-label="Close point details"
            >
              ×
            </button>
            <div class="map-point-content" id="mapPointContent"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="map-legend">
            <span class="map-legend-item"><span class="map-dot"></span> Journey stops</span>
            <span class="map-legend-item"><span class="map-dot muted"></span> Churches</span>
            <span class="map-legend-item"><span class="map-dot hollow"></span> Low confidence</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-toast" id="mapToast" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
  </section>

  <details class="map-about" id="map-about">
    <summary>About Map (Beta)</summary>
    <div class="map-about-content">
      <section class="hero-section map-hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <div class="hero-badge">
            <span class="hero-badge-text">Map MVP</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="hero-title">Build confidence in place</h2>
          <p class="hero-description">
            Map turns where into a study tool. Follow Paul's journeys, surface key early churches,
            and connect passages to geography without losing the reading-first experience.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="hero-cta primary" href="#map-workspace">Explore Paul's Journeys</a>
            <a class="hero-cta secondary" href="#map-features">See MVP scope</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stats map-hero-stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-number">4</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Journey routes</div>
              <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts 13-28</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-number">50+</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Places</div>
              <div class="stat-sublabel">MVP scope</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="stat-number">8</div>
              <div class="stat-label">Church hubs</div>
              <div class="stat-sublabel">Acts + epistles</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="map-section" id="map-features">
        <div class="map-section-header">
          <div>
            <h2>What the MVP includes</h2>
            <p>
              Start with Paul's journeys and the early church network. Every element is built to
              support reading, not replace it.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-badge">MVP Scope</div>
        </div>

        <div class="map-feature-grid">
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Journey routes</h3>
            <p>Pick Journey 1-3 or To Rome and step through ordered stops with Acts references.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Stop-by-stop focus</h3>
            <p>Use next/previous controls to jump between cities and return to the text in one click.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Ancient churches</h3>
            <p>Toggle key communities like Antioch, Corinth, Ephesus, and Rome with profile panels.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Chapter-aware defaults</h3>
            <p>Open the map from Acts 13-28 and the relevant stops are already filtered.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Modern labels</h3>
            <p>Optional modern place labels keep orientation clear without overwhelming the map.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-feature-card">
            <h3>Bookmarkable views</h3>
            <p>Save a place, a journey, or a full map state to revisit later.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="map-section map-entry" id="map-entry">
        <div class="map-section-header">
          <div>
            <h2>Entry points</h2>
            <p>Map lives in the top nav and also appears inside Acts pages for instant context.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="map-entry-grid">
          <div class="map-entry-card">
            <h3>Top nav: Map</h3>
            <p>Start with a focused landing page that defaults to Paul's journeys (MVP).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-entry-card">
            <h3>Acts book page</h3>
            <p>Use a dedicated CTA: "View Paul's journeys on Map".</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-entry-card">
            <h3>Acts chapter pages</h3>
            <p>Open directly to that chapter's places with a filtered stop list.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="map-section map-next">
        <div class="map-section-header">
          <div>
            <h2>Next after MVP</h2>
            <p>Expand to OT routes, tribal boundaries, and multi-era overlays with confidence labels.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="map-next-grid">
          <div class="map-next-card">
            <h3>OT routes</h3>
            <p>Exodus, exile, and return paths with model variants.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-next-card">
            <h3>Tribes by era</h3>
            <p>Timeline slider for shifting tribal territories.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="map-next-card">
            <h3>Empires + provinces</h3>
            <p>Roman, Persian, and Greek overlays with confidence cues.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>

<script type="module" src="/assets/js/map/index.js"></script>
